                                     Types

PMouse
       A pointer to object type TMouse.

TMouse
       The object used for FSMouse;




                            Procedures and Functions


constructor TMouse.Init

         MUST be called before any other FSMouse routine.  Checks to see if a
   mouse driver is installed.  If not, then halts program execution.

procedure TMouse.HideMouse

         Hides the mouse cursor.  Should be called before any writing is done
   on the screen.

procedure TMouse.ShowMouse

         Shows the mouse cursor.  Must be called after a call to HideMouse to
   show the mouse cursor again.

function TMouse.GetNumberOfButtons : byte

         Returns the number of buttons on the mouse.

function TMouse.ButtonPressed : byte

         Returns 0 if no button pressed, otherwise returns 1 for left button,
   2 for right button and 3 for middle button.

function TMouse.GetX : word

         Returns X (horizontal) coordinates of mouse for 80x25 text mode.

function TMouse.GetY : word

         Returns Y (vertical) coordinates of mouse for 80x25 text mode.

destructor TMouse.Done

         Shuts down TMouse.





